## Open Questions

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q1: Attendance Recovery / Critical Attendance notification generation logic?**
> These two new types are required in the enum but no generation logic currently exists. Should I implement generation triggers for these?
> - **Attendance Recovery**: fire when a subject crosses from below ‚Üí above the goal threshold?
> - **Critical Attendance**: fire when attendance drops below a "critical" threshold (e.g. 60%)?
> Or should these remain as enum values only (reserved for future implementation)?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q2: Should `classReminder` and `attendanceMarking` write to the Notification Center?**
> These are high-frequency (daily, per-class). Writing them to Firestore means the center fills with dozens of entries per week. Recommendation: **do NOT** write these to Firestore ‚Äî they are device-level transient reminders, not persistent history. Confirm?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q3: `NotificationPagination` keepAlive vs AutoDispose?**
> Making it `keepAlive()` means it persists for the app session (fast re-opens). AutoDispose resets on every navigation pop (clean but shows loading flash). **Recommendation: keepAlive** for duration of auth session, dispose on logout. Confirm?

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Q4: "Clear All" scope?**
> Should "Clear All" delete all notifications from Firestore permanently, or just hide them (mark all read)? Deleting is permanent and irreversible.
